1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,279
Thank you, it's been wonderful.

2
00:00:01,279 --> 00:00:02,680
I've certainly been blessed

3
00:00:02,680 --> 00:00:04,960
and I hope that you have as well.

4
00:00:04,960 --> 00:00:07,800
And we've had the opportunity to hear through song

5
00:00:07,800 --> 00:00:09,279
and also through the program,

6
00:00:09,279 --> 00:00:12,199
the wonderful story of Christmas.

7
00:00:12,199 --> 00:00:15,520
And really Christmas is the celebration of Christ's birth.

8
00:00:15,520 --> 00:00:19,000
We've read of that already in the Gospel of Matthew

9
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:21,120
and also in the Gospel of Luke.

10
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:24,920
And John says it this way in John one in verse number 14,

11
00:00:24,920 --> 00:00:28,920
the word was made flesh and dwelt among us.

12
00:00:28,920 --> 00:00:31,360
And what a great declaration that is.

13
00:00:31,360 --> 00:00:33,040
This evening for just a few moments,

14
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,959
I wanna focus on how John states it

15
00:00:35,959 --> 00:00:39,360
in the epistle of first John chapter four

16
00:00:39,360 --> 00:00:41,259
and verse number 14.

17
00:00:41,259 --> 00:00:44,240
I believe that this verse so adequately summarizes

18
00:00:44,240 --> 00:00:45,880
the message of Christmas.

19
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:48,639
In first John four and verse number 14,

20
00:00:48,639 --> 00:00:50,400
the Bible says this,

21
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:54,680
and we have seen and do testify

22
00:00:54,680 --> 00:00:59,680
that the father sent the son to be the savior of the world.

23
00:01:00,680 --> 00:01:03,240
Isn't that a wonderful verse of scripture?

24
00:01:03,240 --> 00:01:04,639
As I read that verse,

25
00:01:04,639 --> 00:01:07,599
I find that the reason that Christ was sent

26
00:01:07,599 --> 00:01:09,379
is clearly declared for us

27
00:01:09,379 --> 00:01:12,760
and it is to be the savior of the world.

28
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:15,279
That word savior is such an important word

29
00:01:15,279 --> 00:01:16,680
for us to understand.

30
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:21,680
And we find that the word means one that saves or preserves,

31
00:01:22,080 --> 00:01:26,199
but properly can only be applied to the Lord Jesus Christ.

32
00:01:26,199 --> 00:01:30,599
This is according to the Noah Webster's 1828 dictionary.

33
00:01:30,599 --> 00:01:35,519
It says properly applied only to Jesus Christ, the redeemer,

34
00:01:35,519 --> 00:01:40,199
who has opened the way to everlasting salvation

35
00:01:40,199 --> 00:01:43,160
by his obedience and death

36
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:46,559
and who is therefore called the savior

37
00:01:46,559 --> 00:01:51,559
by way of distinction, the savior of the world.

38
00:01:52,239 --> 00:01:54,160
Begin to think about this statement,

39
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:57,279
this declaration in first John four and verse number 14.

40
00:01:57,279 --> 00:02:02,199
And we find that there's obviously a need for a savior.

41
00:02:02,199 --> 00:02:05,260
And this need is a universal need.

42
00:02:05,260 --> 00:02:09,240
The Bible says that he would be the savior of the world.

43
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:13,399
That's not talking about the rocks and the dirt

44
00:02:13,399 --> 00:02:14,240
and the trees.

45
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:15,720
That's talking about the people

46
00:02:16,639 --> 00:02:20,520
that God would be the savior of the world.

47
00:02:20,520 --> 00:02:22,960
I would say this, not only is it a universal need,

48
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:25,679
but it's the greatest need of humanity.

49
00:02:25,679 --> 00:02:27,160
It's a universal need.

50
00:02:27,160 --> 00:02:28,240
It's for the entire world,

51
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:31,020
but it's the greatest need as individuals.

52
00:02:31,020 --> 00:02:33,520
We need a savior.

53
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:37,139
I was pondering the truth of Luke chapter number one,

54
00:02:37,139 --> 00:02:40,520
verses 46 and 47, where Mary says this.

55
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:42,240
It says, and Mary said,

56
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:45,919
my soul doth magnify the Lord

57
00:02:45,919 --> 00:02:48,479
and my spirit hath rejoiced.

58
00:02:48,479 --> 00:02:52,839
Notice this, in God, my savior.

59
00:02:53,679 --> 00:02:57,119
I notice in first John chapter four and verse number 14,

60
00:02:57,119 --> 00:03:00,600
that John says, and we have seen and do testify

61
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:05,600
that the father sent the son to be the savior of the world.

62
00:03:05,919 --> 00:03:10,919
And Mary says, my spirit hath rejoiced in God, my savior.

63
00:03:10,979 --> 00:03:13,679
So the question this evening is very simple.

64
00:03:13,679 --> 00:03:18,220
How does the savior of the world become my savior?

65
00:03:19,199 --> 00:03:24,199
How does the savior of the world become my savior?

66
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:25,720
Jesus was born.

67
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:26,880
We celebrate that.

68
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:28,240
We are here this evening.

69
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,479
We've seen so many things.

70
00:03:29,479 --> 00:03:30,600
We've heard so many things.

71
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:33,820
He was born, but he didn't stay a baby.

72
00:03:33,820 --> 00:03:36,800
He lived a perfect, sinless life.

73
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:39,119
He was born to die.

74
00:03:39,119 --> 00:03:41,199
We find that after his public ministry,

75
00:03:41,199 --> 00:03:45,279
he went to a cruel cross and it was there that he died

76
00:03:45,279 --> 00:03:48,399
and he shed his blood for the sins of humanity,

77
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:50,559
for your sin and for my sin.

78
00:03:50,559 --> 00:03:51,399
Why?

79
00:03:51,399 --> 00:03:55,160
Because God sent him to be the savior of the world.

80
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:57,880
And in order to save, he had to die.

81
00:03:57,880 --> 00:03:59,919
He had to shed his blood

82
00:03:59,919 --> 00:04:03,639
because there had to be a payment for sin.

83
00:04:03,639 --> 00:04:05,039
The Bible says it this way,

84
00:04:05,039 --> 00:04:09,399
for he hath made him to be sin for us who knew no sin,

85
00:04:09,399 --> 00:04:14,199
that we might be made the righteousness of God in him.

86
00:04:14,199 --> 00:04:16,559
We find that three days later,

87
00:04:16,559 --> 00:04:21,000
he rose triumphantly conquering sin, death, and the grave.

88
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:25,119
He's alive forevermore, hallelujah.

89
00:04:25,119 --> 00:04:28,679
But I find that his precious blood was shed

90
00:04:29,619 --> 00:04:33,119
to make a payment for your sin and for my sin.

91
00:04:33,119 --> 00:04:35,440
We heard a little bit this evening about gifts

92
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:38,640
and maybe some of you have already purchased some gifts

93
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:39,760
for some loved ones.

94
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:41,480
And when you purchased that gift,

95
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:45,200
you had to pay for it in order to give it to someone else.

96
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:47,000
And I want you to know that the gift

97
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:52,000
that God offers to humanity is the gift of eternal life.

98
00:04:52,359 --> 00:04:55,119
The Bible says that the gift of God is eternal life

99
00:04:55,119 --> 00:04:58,579
through Jesus Christ, our Lord.

100
00:04:58,579 --> 00:05:01,260
That gift had to be paid for as well,

101
00:05:01,260 --> 00:05:04,140
but we cannot pay for that gift.

102
00:05:04,140 --> 00:05:05,880
You can't be a good enough person.

103
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:07,220
You can't work enough.

104
00:05:07,220 --> 00:05:09,040
Religion can't save you.

105
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:10,440
Works can't save you.

106
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:14,519
Jesus Christ paid the price.

107
00:05:14,519 --> 00:05:17,600
And the only price that was acceptable

108
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:22,000
was the shed blood of God himself.

109
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,200
And what a blessing to understand that.

110
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:26,640
When I think about the gift of eternal life,

111
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:29,959
I would say this tonight, the gift is essential.

112
00:05:29,959 --> 00:05:31,480
What do I mean by that?

113
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:33,679
You need this gift.

114
00:05:33,679 --> 00:05:35,559
You absolutely need this gift.

115
00:05:35,559 --> 00:05:38,519
I understand we live in a marketing society

116
00:05:38,519 --> 00:05:41,459
and they will try to market to you what you need

117
00:05:41,459 --> 00:05:43,600
and it will make your life happy and easier

118
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:45,000
and so on and so forth.

119
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:47,799
But the gift of God that is eternal life,

120
00:05:47,799 --> 00:05:51,000
you need this gift.

121
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,799
Without this gift, the Bible tells us

122
00:05:53,799 --> 00:05:56,420
that we'll spend eternity in a lake of fire.

123
00:05:56,420 --> 00:05:57,260
Why?

124
00:05:57,260 --> 00:05:59,160
Because sin must be paid for.

125
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:01,600
If you don't accept the gift,

126
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:05,119
then the just God issues the punishment

127
00:06:05,119 --> 00:06:08,239
and that's eternal separation from all of eternity.

128
00:06:08,239 --> 00:06:10,459
That's the truth of God's word.

129
00:06:10,459 --> 00:06:12,160
But he loves you.

130
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:14,160
We heard about the message of love.

131
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,519
Christmas, the message of love.

132
00:06:15,519 --> 00:06:17,640
He loves you that he died for you

133
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:20,000
and he offers you this gift.

134
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,279
It's essential.

135
00:06:21,279 --> 00:06:23,640
But I would say this, it's exclusive.

136
00:06:23,640 --> 00:06:26,399
You hear sometimes about an exclusive offer.

137
00:06:26,399 --> 00:06:28,239
You can only buy this thing at this place.

138
00:06:28,239 --> 00:06:30,579
Can I tell you that the gift of eternal life

139
00:06:30,579 --> 00:06:33,959
is only available through Jesus Christ

140
00:06:33,959 --> 00:06:36,660
and his shed blood on the cross of Calvary.

141
00:06:36,660 --> 00:06:40,399
Jesus Christ said, I am the way, the truth, and the life.

142
00:06:40,399 --> 00:06:43,359
No man cometh unto the Father but by me.

143
00:06:43,359 --> 00:06:45,440
He did not say, I am a way.

144
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:47,320
He said, I am the way.

145
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:50,700
And we find that this gift, it's essential, it's exclusive.

146
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:53,880
When I think about the gift of God, which is eternal life,

147
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:57,559
I want you to understand this evening that it was paid for

148
00:06:57,559 --> 00:07:00,279
and it's available to you this evening.

149
00:07:00,279 --> 00:07:01,619
It's available.

150
00:07:01,619 --> 00:07:02,940
We ask this question,

151
00:07:02,940 --> 00:07:07,399
how does the savior of the world become my savior?

152
00:07:08,399 --> 00:07:11,079
It was 28 years ago in my life

153
00:07:11,079 --> 00:07:13,480
where I recognized that I was a sinner

154
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:15,440
and Christ was the only savior.

155
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:19,959
I was guilty and I deserved punishment.

156
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:24,160
But Jesus Christ, God himself, took my place.

157
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:27,519
He paid for my sin and he offered me the gift.

158
00:07:27,519 --> 00:07:29,679
The Bible says this, that he came to his own

159
00:07:29,679 --> 00:07:32,079
and his own received him not,

160
00:07:32,079 --> 00:07:35,480
but as many as received him, to them gave he power

161
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:36,720
to become the sons of God,

162
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:40,079
even to them that believe on his name.

163
00:07:40,079 --> 00:07:41,880
So this evening, very simply,

164
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:44,799
how does the savior of the world become your savior?

165
00:07:44,799 --> 00:07:49,519
By you accepting him as your personal Lord and savior,

166
00:07:49,519 --> 00:07:51,559
recognizing that you're a sinner,

167
00:07:51,559 --> 00:07:53,239
that religion can't save you,

168
00:07:53,239 --> 00:07:54,959
that your works can't save you,

169
00:07:54,959 --> 00:07:58,160
that the only way to be saved

170
00:07:58,160 --> 00:07:59,820
and to know that heaven is your home

171
00:07:59,820 --> 00:08:02,160
is through the shed blood of Jesus Christ

172
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,640
on the cross of Calvary.

173
00:08:03,679 --> 00:08:05,600
And here's the exciting news.

174
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:07,820
If you've never accepted that free gift,

175
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:10,640
you can accept that gift this evening.

176
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:13,079
I would encourage you, don't leave here this evening

177
00:08:13,079 --> 00:08:16,160
without knowing for sure that heaven is your home,

178
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:19,920
having that 100% confidence

179
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:24,119
that the savior of the world is my savior.

180
00:08:24,119 --> 00:08:27,920
And you need to know that the Lord is your savior.

181
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:31,519
The psalmist said this, the Lord is my shepherd.

182
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:35,679
He ends the psalm, a very familiar psalm in Psalm 23,

183
00:08:35,679 --> 00:08:38,539
and I will dwell in the house of the Lord forever.

184
00:08:38,539 --> 00:08:39,679
Can I tell you, there's a connection

185
00:08:39,679 --> 00:08:41,340
between verse one and six.

186
00:08:42,359 --> 00:08:44,159
You'll only dwell in the house of the Lord forever

187
00:08:44,159 --> 00:08:47,640
if the Lord is your shepherd, personally.

188
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:51,080
He is the great shepherd, he is the good shepherd.

189
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:53,659
But the question is, can you say he's my shepherd?

190
00:08:53,659 --> 00:08:58,400
Can we say, as Mary said, my savior?

191
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:00,280
This evening, if you're not sure of heaven,

192
00:09:00,280 --> 00:09:02,039
if you've never accepted Jesus Christ

193
00:09:02,039 --> 00:09:05,479
as your personal savior, tonight he offers you the gift

194
00:09:05,479 --> 00:09:07,559
and all you have to do is receive it.

195
00:09:07,559 --> 00:09:10,200
We're gonna pray and then we're gonna sing one last song.

196
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,320
And so if you would close your eyes and bow your heads,

197
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:13,640
we're gonna pray just for a moment.

198
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:16,239
Lord, we love you, we thank you for loving us,

199
00:09:16,239 --> 00:09:20,219
we thank you for the gift of eternal life.

200
00:09:20,219 --> 00:09:23,119
So often we think about gifts during the Christmas season

201
00:09:23,119 --> 00:09:25,000
and all that's taking place,

202
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:28,000
but we think of that greatest gift.

203
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,880
God, you sent forth your son

204
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:32,760
to be the savior of the world.

205
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:35,799
And tonight I hope that not one person would leave here

206
00:09:35,799 --> 00:09:37,940
without knowing that the savior of the world

207
00:09:37,940 --> 00:09:40,119
is their savior personally.

208
00:09:40,119 --> 00:09:42,880
I'm gonna ask you a question, I'm not gonna embarrass you,

209
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:44,419
I don't want anyone looking around,

210
00:09:44,419 --> 00:09:46,159
but if you're here this evening,

211
00:09:46,159 --> 00:09:48,900
and I'd never call you out, I'd never try to embarrass you,

212
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:52,760
but if you'd say, pastor, I do not know

213
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:54,960
that God is my savior.

214
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:58,840
I've never accepted Jesus Christ as my personal savior.

215
00:09:58,840 --> 00:10:01,400
The thought of death scares me.

216
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:03,559
I do not have assurance that I'd go to heaven

217
00:10:03,559 --> 00:10:04,640
if I were to die.

218
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:06,960
If that's you this evening, would you just slip your hand up

219
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:08,919
I'd never call on you, I'd never embarrass you,

220
00:10:08,919 --> 00:10:10,419
I just wanna pray for you.

221
00:10:10,419 --> 00:10:12,140
You say, pastor, I'm not sure of heaven,

222
00:10:12,140 --> 00:10:13,059
would you pray for me?

223
00:10:13,059 --> 00:10:14,539
Anyone at all?

224
00:10:14,539 --> 00:10:15,380
Anyone at all?

225
00:10:15,380 --> 00:10:17,159
I'm not 100% sure of heaven.

226
00:10:18,559 --> 00:10:19,960
Anyone else?

227
00:10:19,960 --> 00:10:21,520
Some have raised their hands.

228
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:23,520
Let me say this to you this evening.

229
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:24,859
If you're not sure of heaven,

230
00:10:24,859 --> 00:10:26,219
you could pray a prayer like this.

231
00:10:26,219 --> 00:10:28,719
It's not the prayer that saves you,

232
00:10:28,719 --> 00:10:30,159
but you could pray a prayer like this.

233
00:10:30,159 --> 00:10:35,159
Lord, I know that I'm a sinner and I deserve judgment,

234
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:37,340
but I understand that Jesus Christ died

235
00:10:37,340 --> 00:10:40,820
on the cross of Calvary so that I could be saved.

236
00:10:40,820 --> 00:10:44,599
He paid for my sin and I accept the free gift

237
00:10:44,599 --> 00:10:47,080
of eternal life this night.

238
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:50,200
I ask Christ to be my savior, amen.

239
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:52,239
If you prayed that this evening,

240
00:10:52,239 --> 00:10:54,039
the Bible says for whosoever shall call

241
00:10:54,039 --> 00:10:57,119
upon the name of the Lord shall be saved.

242
00:10:57,119 --> 00:11:00,200
And what a joy to know this Christmas

243
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:02,239
that heaven is your home.

244
00:11:02,239 --> 00:11:05,359
Father, I pray that as these that have raised their hands,

245
00:11:05,359 --> 00:11:07,159
that they would know with certainty

246
00:11:07,159 --> 00:11:08,320
that heaven is their home,

247
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:12,159
that you'd give us opportunity to be able to speak with them

248
00:11:12,159 --> 00:11:13,659
and Lord, we'll thank you for it.

249
00:11:13,659 --> 00:11:15,359
Thank you so much for the privilege

250
00:11:15,359 --> 00:11:16,440
of being here this evening.

251
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:17,960
Bless the remainder of the service

252
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:21,400
for it's in Christ's name we pray, amen.

253
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:22,239
We have.

